                                    <!-- FAQ Section for AEO -->
                                    <div class="faq-section" style="margin-top: 40px;">
                                        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                                        <h3>How do I get cited by ChatGPT, Claude or Perplexity?</h3>
                                        <p>Use question-format H2s with 60-100 word concise answer paragraphs, FAQPage schema on every guide page, TL;DR boxes at the top, and Article + Person schema for E-E-A-T signal. Allow GPTBot, ClaudeBot, PerplexityBot in robots.txt. First citations appear in 30-90 days for focused implementation.</p>
                                        <h3>Which AI search engine drives the most referral traffic in 2026?</h3>
                                        <p>Perplexity drives the most direct click-through (live-web with prominent citation links). ChatGPT and Claude drive less click-through but more brand-mention impressions. Google AI Overviews drives traffic similar to traditional rich results. Track all four in GA4 referrers.</p>
                                        <h3>Should I create separate content for AI search vs traditional SEO?</h3>
                                        <p>No. The same well-structured content wins both. Layer AI-search optimisation (schema, question format, TL;DR, FAQ) on top of solid SEO content. Splitting investment across two content sets is wasteful and rarely outperforms a single well-optimised version.</p>
                                        <h3>How long does AI-search optimisation take to show results?</h3>
                                        <p>First citation lifts in 30-90 days for focused implementation. Measurable AI-referral traffic in GA4 in 6 months. Material lead impact in 12 months. Faster on already-authoritative domains; slower on new sites with weak backlink profiles.</p>
                                        <h3>What's the single highest-impact change I can make today?</h3>
                                        <p>Add FAQPage schema with 5-7 Q&As to your top 10 organic-traffic pages, with each H2 in question format. This single change has lifted citation frequency 2-4x in our 2025-26 client engagements.</p>
